===Etymology===
Probably from {{etyl|enm}} {{term|melsche|lang=enm}}, {{term|molsh||soft|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|melsc|lang=ang}}, {{term|milisc||mellow, mild|lang=ang}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/mʌltʃ/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|es|-}}

# {{uncountable|agriculture}} [[shred|Shredded]] vegetable (or occasionally mineral) matter used to cover the top [[layer]] of [[soil]] to protect, insulate, or decorate it, or to discourage [[weed]]s or retain [[moisture]].
#: ''An organic '''mulch''' is a '''mulch''' made of natural substances such as leaves or grass clippings.''
# {{countable|agriculture}} A material used as mulch, as ''a decorative redwood bark mulch.''

